Přindiš, Prskavec and Fišerová safely advanced to the semi-finals of the World Championships
Kayakers Vít Přindiš and Jiří Prskavec and canoeist Tereza Fišerová safely advanced to the semi-finals of the World Slalom Championships in Seu d'Urgell. Prindiš was fourth, Prskavec fifth and Fišerová eighth in Friday's qualification. Three more Czech athletes will be in Spain to try to reach the semi-finals in the afternoon qualifying heat.
Vavrinec Hradilek failed to make it out of the strong group of national kayakers, receiving a fifty-second penalty for a misjudgement at the start of the heat. Přindiš and Prskavec, on the other hand, can rest and concentrate on Sunday's semi-final.
"I set myself the goal of making it to the top 30 in the first run, which I managed to do. It's not that I didn't care how I finished, because Sunday's start is very early in the morning, so I was hoping to be a little higher to get a better starting position," said Přindiš, praising his comfort in Seu. "Before the patrol race I felt the worst I've felt in the 14 days we've been here. But then during the race it was good and today it was better again. It's beautiful here all the time, nice races, the spectators came, so it's good," he smiled.
Prskavec was also happy. "In qualifying you don't want to make any unnecessary mistakes. In the first gates I was not good at all. Then I drove the middle very well, without any problems and I knew I had mileage, so the second mistake came when I wanted to go down the straight and I turned the wheel. Overall, I can't be unhappy. The form is there, let's see how it goes," said this year's overall World Cup winner.
Both athletes praised the fact that they will go for the start at the end of the semi-final block on Sunday. "I'm not an early bird, plus it's cold here in the mornings and when you're here at eight o'clock you need a jacket and a sweatshirt," said Prindiš. "All in all, the semifinals take an hour and a half, which is a pretty good difference in terms of sleep," Prskavec agreed.
Of the three Czech women's singles canoeists, only Fišerová succeeded, Eva Říhová finished two places behind the top 20, while Kateřina Havlíčková was 35th. "I did the upper part as I wanted, in the middle passage I felt like I was not keeping up and not going according to plan, but I managed to get into a comfortable track that I wanted to ride. I made two shuffles and I'm just behind the winner with a clear time. I have a good starting position for the semi-final," praised Fischer.
