Project Management Methodology means the principles by which the provision of Services is organised. The Project Management Methodology sets out the binding rules governing the management, coordination and control activities in the provision of the Services in accordance with the contractual arrangements between the Client and the Contractor. The Project Management Methodology shall be discussed, supplemented, amended and approved by the Parties in the Project Charter. The Project Management Methodology is contained in Annex 6 (Project Management Methodology).
Civil Code means Act No. 89/2012 Coll., the Civil Code, as amended.
Remuneration means the Contractor's remuneration for the provision of the Services.  The method of calculation of the Remuneration is set out in Appendix 2 (Remuneration).
Eligible Entity means the Client and any entity directly or indirectly controlled by any of the ultimate owners of the Client.
Patch means an incremental change to the Application that addresses Category A or B Incidents in the Operational Environment or Category TA or TB or TC Incidents in the Acceptance Environment. A Patch is for a specific Upgrade or Patch, respectively. The Patch also includes the relevant Documentation. A Patch can only be deployed in conjunction with the Upgrade or Patch for which it is intended. The order of Patches is defined by the Contractor and must be followed during deployment.
Business Day means any day other than Saturday and Sunday and days on which a public holiday or other holiday falls according to the valid and effective legislation of the Czech Republic.
Working Hour means 60 minutes during the time the Contractor is required to provide the Service.
Delivery Cover Sheet means a document containing information on the details of the Delivery and information necessary for its application to the Client's technological environment.
Redmine means the dedicated portion of the Redmine information system for the Application at helpdesk.jtfg.com
