Service means each of the services listed in Schedule 1 (Services).
Works Contract means the contract entered into between the Contractor and the Client as set out in Schedule 13 (Contracts of Work). The subject matter of the Works Contract is the execution of the Works on the basis of the Change Documents. The Contract for the Work shall commence at the time when the Client accepts the Contractor's offer in the form of the Change Documents. The Work Contract cannot be concluded orally. The contents of the Contract for Work, unless the Parties agree otherwise in a particular case, shall be governed by Appendix 13 (Contents of the Contract for Work).
Specification means a precise description of the Application, its features, functionalities and user interface, which forms Annex 3 (Description of the Application Components and Documentation).
Upgrade means an incremental change to the Application that enables the deployment of new functionality, a change to existing functionality or a change to the data in the Application from the current state of the Application. An Upgrade consists of those elements of the Version in which there is a change from the current state of the Application. The Upgrade shall also include a description of how to test for the new functionality contained therein. The current state of the Application is obtained by installing the most recently delivered Version and all subsequent Upgrades, and as part of the deployment of the Upgrade, all Patches that have been created since the previous Upgrade are also deployed, except those that have not modified the functionality and/or control data of the Application. The relevant Documentation is also part of the Upgrade. The Upgrade shall include changes to the Application specified by the Customer and implemented on the basis of the Change Documentation and the resolution of Category C Incidents.
Version means a complete state of the Application in a form that allows for complete and independent installation of the Application, including its settings, to provide functionality as defined in the Specification and operational settings. A Version includes (1) a version of the Application in the form of executable code; and (2) the operational settings of the Application; and (3) the documentation for the Application.
Change Control is the process by which changes to the Application and Documentation are made. The Change Procedure results in a change to the Application and Documentation that is consistent with the Change Request.
