10. Acceptance Procedure, Delivery of Upgrade to Acceptance Procedure
10.1 The purpose of the Acceptance Procedure is to verify that the result of the Contractor's activities is in accordance with the Specification and Change Documents for the Changes included in the Upgrade Delivery. Furthermore, the purpose of the Acceptance Procedure is to verify that the Incidents included in the Upgrade Delivery are resolved.
10.2 The elements and steps of the Acceptance Procedure are set out in Appendix 9 (Acceptance Procedure). The Acceptance Procedure includes the acceptance criteria that the Upgrade Delivery must meet.
10.3 If the Contractor demonstrates the result of its activities under this Agreement to the Client and demonstrates the results of the unit and integration tests it has performed on such result, the Contractor shall submit the result of its activities to the Client for the Acceptance Procedure.
10.4 The Parties shall draw up a record of the submission of the result of the Contractor's activities to the Acceptance Procedure. The Contractor shall submit a draft of the Minute of Handover of the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure. The draft Record of Submission of the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure shall always include the result of the unit and integration tests. The model of the Record of Handover of the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure is contained in Annex 10 (Model Record of Handover of the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure).
11. Commencement, conduct and termination of the Upgrade Delivery Acceptance Procedure
11.1 Without undue delay after the Parties have signed the Record of Delivery of the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure, the Parties shall agree a timetable for the execution of the Acceptance Procedure and the Customer shall commence the Acceptance Procedure.
11.2 During the course of the Acceptance Procedure, the Client shall make a list of Incidents that have affected the Contractor's performance, compared to the required performance of the Upgrade Delivery, and submit this list to the Contractor. The Client may also report Incidents to the Contractor during the course of the Acceptance Procedure. During the Acceptance Procedure, the Contractor may resolve the Incidents, rectify the defects and, in accordance with the agreed procedures, submit the corrected result of its activities to the Client for further implementation of the Acceptance Procedure.
11.3 The Acceptance Procedure is terminated either:
11.3.1 completion of all steps of the Acceptance Procedure, resolution of all reported Incidents and rectification of all identified defects in the Upgrade Delivery; or
11.3.2 the end of the period specified in the agreed timetable for the implementation of the Acceptance Procedure; or
11.3.3 if, during the course of the Acceptance Procedure, the number of Incidents which are Defects exceeds the number of Defects specified in the Acceptance Criteria which gives the Customer the right to stop the Acceptance Procedure.
12. Successful completion of the Acceptance Procedure for the Upgrade Delivery
12.1 If all steps of the Acceptance Procedure have been completed, and if the Upgrade Delivery meets all of the Acceptance Criteria set out in Annex 9 (Acceptance Procedure), and if by the end of the Acceptance Procedure the Contractor has resolved all reported Upgrade Incidents and remedied all identified Upgrade Defects, the Acceptance Procedure shall be terminated as successful without reservation.
12.2 If all steps of the Acceptance Procedure have been completed and the Upgrade Delivery meets all of the acceptance criteria set out in Annex 9 (Acceptance Procedure), and if by the end of the Acceptance Procedure the Contractor has not resolved all reported Incidents of the result of its activities and has not remedied all identified defects in the result of its activities, the Acceptance Procedure shall be terminated as successful with reservations.
12.3 If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as successful, the Parties shall execute a Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for use. The Contractor shall submit a draft Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for use. If the Upgrade Delivery has defects, the draft of such record shall always include a list of the defects and the required date for their rectification. No later than one (1) week after the date on which the Client has agreed to the draft Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use, the Parties shall sign the Record. A specimen of such Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Supply for Use is attached as Annex 11 (Specimen Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Supply for Use).
12.4 If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as successful subject to the removal of defects, the Contractor shall remove all defects within the time periods specified in the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use. The Contractor shall submit the corrected Delivery to the Client for re-verification. If the Contractor fails to remedy all defects within the time limits specified in the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use, the Contractor shall be in default.
12.5 By signing the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use (1) the Customer confirms that at the time of signing such record the Upgrade Delivery is free from defects that prevent the use of the Application and (2) the Contractor declares that the Upgrade Delivery is made in accordance with the Specification and the Change Documentation of the Changes incorporated into the Upgrade and Czech law. The moment at which the last Party signs the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for use is the moment at which (1) the Contractor has fulfilled its obligation to perform the Delivery and (2) the Client acquires ownership of the Delivery.
12.6 Even if the Client is in default in accepting the Upgrade Delivery, the Contractor shall not have the right to sell the Upgrade Delivery to a third party. If the Client accepts the Upgrade Delivery, the rights arising from an apparent defect in the Upgrade Delivery remain with the Client, even if the Contractor argues to the court that the right was not exercised in time.
13. Failure to complete the Acceptance Procedure for the Upgrade Delivery
13.1 If the Upgrade Delivery does not meet the acceptance criteria set out in Appendix 9 (Acceptance Procedure) the Acceptance Procedure shall be terminated as unsuccessful. The Acceptance Procedure shall also be terminated as unsuccessful if, during the course of the Acceptance Procedure, the number of defects identified by the Customer exceeds the number of defects specified in the Acceptance Criteria which gives the Customer the right to stop the Acceptance Procedure. If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as unsuccessful, the Client shall list the defects that have become apparent in the Upgrade Deliverable submitted for the Acceptance Procedure and return this list, together with the Upgrade Deliverable, to the Contractor.
13.2 If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as unsuccessful, the Contractor shall be deemed not to have submitted the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure. The relevant Record of Submission of the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure shall be treated as if it had never been created.
13.3 If the Contractor fails to submit the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure in time, the Contractor shall be in default.
13.4 If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as unsuccessful, the Contractor shall as soon as possible rectify the defects which led to the termination of the Acceptance Procedure as unsuccessful and submit the corrected Upgrade Delivery to the Client for a repeat Acceptance Procedure. The cost of the re-acceptance procedure shall be borne by the Contractor.
14. Patch Delivery Acceptance Procedure
14.1 The purpose of the Acceptance Procedure is to verify that the Contractor's actions have resulted in the resolution of the Incident or Incidents included in the Patch Delivery.
14.2 The elements and steps of the Acceptance Procedure are set out in Appendix 9 (Acceptance Procedure). The Acceptance Procedure includes the acceptance criteria that the Patch Delivery must meet.
