Annex 6 / Project Management Methodology
1. Project Charter
1.1 The purpose of the Project Charter is to define the formal management processes and communication arrangements between the Parties for the purpose of fulfilling the object of the Contract so that the performance of the Work or provision of the Services is in accordance with the Contract and this Project Management Methodology. The Project Charter shall make available to those persons involved in the execution of the Work or the provision of the Services those parts of the Contract that are necessary for the fulfilment of its object. The Project Charter shall specify the composition of the project's organisational structure, the method of communication, the control and escalation mechanisms and the structure of the project portal where all documentation related to the execution of the work or the provision of services shall be archived. The Project Charter shall be drafted by the Project Leads and approved by the Steering Committee at its initial meeting.
2. Organisational structure of the project
2.1 The organizational components of the Project are (1) the Project Steering Committee ("SCP") and (2) the Project Management Team ("PMT") and (3) the Work Teams. The SCP and the PVP are the permanent organizational units of the Project. Work Teams are temporary organizational units of the Project.
Steering Committee
3.1 Powers of the SCP / Steering Committee of the project in particular:
3.1.1 approve the Project Charter; and
3.1.2 resolve escalated issues that have not been resolved at the SCP level; and
3.1.3 resolve issues affecting the scope of work to be performed or services to be provided; and
3.1.4 address issues related to the delivery schedule; and
3.1.5 address issues related to the remuneration or fee structure for the services or work performed; and
3.1.6 accept individual deliveries, services, parts of the work and/or the work as a whole; and
3.2 Members of the SCP / On behalf of the Client, the members of the SCP shall be (1) the Project Sponsor for the Business and (2) the ISIT Division Director and (3) the Project Manager. For the Contractor, the SCP members are (1) the Management Representative and (2) the Project Manager.
3.3 The SCP/SCP shall meet at least quarterly.  The exact days on which the SCP meets regularly shall be determined by the Project Manager in the Project Charter. The SCP shall meet whenever a significant delivery schedule milestone is evaluated (e.g., initiation or completion of the acceptance procedure). The SCP shall meet whenever a Project Leader invites the SCP to meet. The SCP shall meet at the Client's headquarters.
3.4 The SCP meeting agenda / SCP meeting agenda and the papers to be discussed shall be delivered to the SCP members by the Project Manager for the Contractor at least 3 working days prior to the SCP meeting. The SCP meeting shall always discuss the project status report and draft minutes related to the acceptance of the deliverables, services or work.
3.5 Right to Invite Experts and Consultants / If either party deems it necessary, it shall have the right to invite experts or consultants to the SCP meeting, but shall notify the other party in advance, stating the reasons why the presence of experts or consultants at the SCP meeting is advisable.
3.6 Voting / After discussion of each agenda item, SCP members shall vote on the motion that is put forward for that agenda item. Each SCP member shall have one vote.
3.7 SCP Decision Affecting the Contract Terms / If the SCP decision affects the contract terms under which the Work is performed or the Services are provided, in particular if the SCP decision affects the remuneration for which the Work is performed or the Services are provided, the Client shall, without undue delay after such decision is taken, prepare an amendment to the subject contract.
3.8 Minutes / Minutes of the SCP meeting shall be prepared by the Project Manager for the Client and delivered to the Project Manager for the Contractor.
4. Project Management
4.1 Powers of the SCP / The project management of the project shall in particular:
4.1.1 control all deliverables of the various phases of the execution of the Work or provision of the Services; and
4.1.2 evaluate and refine the schedule of deliverables and progress of the Work in the performance of the Work or provision of the Services; and
4.1.3 discuss changes that do not affect the wording of the Contract; and
4.1.4 manage the interaction between the Client and the Contractor; and
4.1.5 manage the risks and remedial actions associated with the performance of the Work or the provision of the Services; and
4.1.6 escalates to the SCP meeting.
4.2 Members of the SCP / On behalf of the Client, the members of the SCP shall be (1) the Project Manager and (2) the Principal Business Analyst and (3) the Application Architect. For the Contractor, the members of the PVP are (1) the Project Manager and (2) the Principal Business Analyst and (3) the Principal Architect.
4.3 The SCP / PVP shall meet weekly, at the Client's site or by remote communication.
4.4 The SCP meeting agenda and supporting documents / The SCP meeting agenda and supporting documents to be discussed shall be delivered to the SCP members by the Project Manager for the Contractor at least 1 working day prior to the SCP meeting.  The PVP shall always discuss at its meeting:
4.4.1 the implementation of open tasks from previous PVPs; and
4.4.2 the progress of the execution of the Work or the provision of the Services; and
4.4.3 the execution and update of the schedule of works; and
4.4.4 the problems identified and how they will be resolved; and
4.4.5 a plan for further action; and
4.4.6 the risks associated with the execution of the work or provision of the services; and
4.4.7 evaluation and other requirements for the Client's cooperation; and
4.4.8 the status and severity of unresolved defects or incidents; and
4.4.9 change requests; and
