Annex 12 / Security Rules
1. Definition of terms
1.1 For the purposes of this Annex, the following terms and phrases shall have the meanings set out below:
Security Incident means any breach of confidentiality, integrity or availability of Information Assets.
Information Asset means any information, process, hardware or software component that (1) supports the business activities of the Entity, or (2) is of value to the Entity, or (3) the disclosure, unauthorized modification or unavailability of which adversely affects the Entity.
Contractor's Persons means persons directly or indirectly involved in the performance of the subject matter of this Agreement, including persons of Contractor's subcontractors.
Authorised Entity's Premises means the premises where the Authorised Entity conducts its business and the information and communication systems used by the Authorised Entity that contain the Information Assets.
2. Personnel Security
2.1 None of the Contractor's Persons:
2.1.1 has a criminal record;
2.1.2 Has no previous conviction for a deliberate criminal offence and is not under criminal prosecution at the time of performance of the subject matter of this Agreement,
2.2 If the Contractor discovers any non-compliance with the above rules by the Contractor's Persons, the Contractor shall immediately inform the Client. The Client shall be entitled to require that such person shall no longer participate in the execution of the work arising from the subject matter of this Agreement, directly or indirectly, and shall be entitled to require the Contractor to provide adequate compensation.
2.3 The Contractor shall provide the Client with a full list of the Contractor's Persons by name. The Contractor undertakes to inform the Client in advance of any changes in the personnel for the performance of this Agreement.
2.4 Contractor's Persons:
2.4.1 shall be familiar with the following safety rules,
2.4.2 have all necessary examinations and certifications as required by law or the requirements of the Regulator for the type of work to be carried out by them in connection with the performance of this Contract,
2.4.3 are regularly trained by the Contractor in areas of information security.
2.5 The Contractor's Persons shall not enter the Authorised Entity's Premises under the influence of addictive, narcotic or psychotropic substances or bring weapons, explosives, combustibles, warfare agents, poisons, radioactive or toxic substances or any other substances endangering human life and/or health.
3. Physical security
3.1 Access by the Contractor's Persons to the Authorised Entity's Premises shall only be permitted if their presence is necessary for the performance of their duties under this Contract.
3.2 The Contractor's Persons shall at all times be accompanied by a responsible employee of the Client in the Authorised Entity's Premises.
3.3 The free movement of the Contractor's Persons in the Authorised Entity's premises is only permitted if the person has been issued with a personal access card. The Contractor's Person shall not lend the access card to third parties or allow third parties access to the Authorised Entity's Premises.
3.4 In the event of loss or suspected loss of the access card, the Contractor shall immediately inform the Client.
3.5 Without undue delay after the completion of the work under this Agreement or the termination of this Agreement, or if further physical access by the Contractor's Persons to the Authorised Entity's Environment is no longer required, the Client shall ensure that all Contractor's Persons return the borrowed Access Cards to the Client.
3.6 No Contractor Person shall remove any Information Assets from the Authorised Entity Environment via storage media without the prior written consent of the Client.
4 Identification and authentication of Contractor Persons in the Authorised Entity Environment
4.1 Contractor's Persons shall only be assigned accounts that uniquely identify the user and only with such permissions as they need to perform their duties under this Agreement.
4.2 The Contractor shall perform routine work tasks under non-privileged accounts and shall only use accounts with administrative privileges when necessary.
4.3 The Contractor's persons shall not access the Internet while working under an account with administrator privileges and/or with applications running under administrator privileges.
4.4 Inactive accounts of Contractor Persons shall be proactively reported by the Contractor to the Client.
4.5 Shared accounts shall only be used by the Contractor with the prior written consent of the Client.
4.6 In the event of a compromised password or suspected compromised password, the Contractor shall immediately ensure that the password is changed or blocked.
5. Handling of certificates
5.1 Access to Certificates (both logical and physical) shall only be granted to those Persons of the Contractor for whom such access is necessary for the performance of their duties.
5.2 The Contractor's Persons shall not provide or make available the Certificates to third parties without the Client's written consent.
5.3 Once installed, the Certificates shall only be stored in secure storage in locations where their storage is necessary for the performance of this Agreement, and all other copies shall be destroyed in a manner that prevents their retrieval.
5.4 Where possible, the private key of the Certificate shall be set to be non-exportable. The private key of the Certificate shall always be protected by a strong password and shall not be stored in unencrypted form.
5.5 The Contractor undertakes to inform the Client immediately of any loss or suspected loss of confidentiality of the private certificate key.
6. Handling of Information Assets
6.1 The handling of Information Assets is restricted to locations that preclude the detection of sensitive information by unauthorised persons. Specifically, it is forbidden to work with Information Assets in means of public transport, in public places and in places where there is a risk of surveillance from industrial cameras.
6.2 Upon completion of the work under this Agreement, the Contractor shall return or remove all Information Assets stored in the Contractor's environment without undue delay, unless possession of such information is required by the laws of the Czech Republic. This applies to both electronic and paper documentation. The removal of the Information Assets shall be carried out in a manner that prevents their recovery.
6.3 The Contractor shall not provide access to the Information Assets to any third parties not entitled to participate in the performance of this Agreement without the prior written consent of the Client.
6.4 The Contractor shall ensure adequate security of the computer equipment on which the Information Assets are stored, processed or transmitted. In connection with the Information Assets, the Contractor shall ensure that in the Contractor's environment:
6.4.1 encryption tools are used to encrypt disks, folders and/or files so as to prevent unauthorised access to the Information Assets,
6.4.2 malicious code detection and removal tools are in use with settings to regularly update the malicious code signature database at a frequency not exceeding one week and appropriate processes are set up for monitoring, logging and responding to positive malicious code detections,
6.4.3 processes are defined, set up, implemented and monitored to update security patches for software components at intervals not exceeding one month from the release of the patches,
6.4.4 the Internet environment is separated by a firewall that is connected to the surveillance and Contractor Persons use only encrypted VPN connections when remotely accessing to prevent unauthorized interception and alteration of transmitted communications.
6.5 Where Information Assets are transferred by the Contractor off the Authorised Entity's premises, the Contractor shall maintain the physical security of such assets and keep such Information Assets under surveillance at all times. The Contractor shall comply with the security and operating instructions of the manufacturer of the hardware on which the Information Assets are processed.
7. Working in an Authorised Entity Environment
7.1 The Contractor shall familiarise itself with and act in accordance with the Information Asset Classification Standard if provided by the Customer.
7.2 For hardware that is owned and managed by the Customer and/or hardware that, including its configuration, has been approved in advance by the Customer, the Contractor shall not make any configuration changes to such hardware that are not approved by the Customer. In particular, the Contractor shall not make changes to the security configuration of the hardware. For each hardware so installed, the process for applying security patches, including the responsibilities of roles within the process, shall be explicitly and formally established.
7.3 The Contractor shall not install and/or run any software not previously approved by the Client without the prior written consent of the Client.
7.4 The Contractor shall not perform any testing of physical or logical security or any type of Authorised Entity controls without the written consent of the Client.
7.5 The Contractor shall not tamper with audit records in any way.
7.6 The Contractor's persons shall not be authorised to handle software, hardware or data content not directly related to the performance of this Agreement.
7.7 Contractor's Persons shall not engage in any activity that is harmful to other individuals or entities, including sending unsolicited emails, sending fraudulent emails, distributing malicious code, or engaging in attacks to disable the availability of the Services.
7.8 All actions taken by the Contractor's Persons shall be logged by the Customer and a record of such actions shall be retained for a period of 3 years.
7.9 The Contractor's Persons shall not connect their own storage devices to any of the Authorised Entity's computing equipment without the written consent of the Customer.
7.10 At the workstation provided, the Contractor's Persons shall, during the time of physical absence:
7.10.1 cleanliness and tidiness so that the workstation can be used safely;
7.10.2 adequate physical security of all Information Assets;
7.10.3 logical locking of access to Information Assets so that unauthorized access to such Information Assets cannot occur.
7.11 The Contractor's Persons shall not, without the prior written consent of the Client, install remote listening devices or make any audio or video recording.
8. Crisis Management
8.1 The Contractor's persons are obliged to prevent, to the greatest extent possible, the occurrence of crisis situations (e.g. fire, explosion, flood, etc.) and situations that could cause injury to persons or damage to the property of the Authorised Person.
8.2 In the event of a crisis situation, the Contractor's Person who is physically present at the scene shall, without exception or delay, comply with the regulations and directives in force in the locality and obey the instructions for evacuation and protection of persons. This also applies in the event of a drill.
8.3 In the event of an emergency, the Contractor's Person shall immediately obey the instructions of the Client's emergency manager.
9. Reporting of security incidents
9.1 If the Contractor Person identifies a security incident, he/she shall report it immediately to the tool https://helpdesk.jtfg.com (telephone: +420 221 710 911).
