2. If, at any time during the term of the lease, the lessee fails to pay the rent or payment for services to which he is obliged in full and on time, this security deposit shall be used by the lessor to cover any arrears.
If the security deposit or part thereof is demonstrably used by the lessor in this way, the lessee shall be obliged to repay the part of the security deposit used so that the security deposit is again in the agreed full amount within 5 days of the date on which the lessor was notified of the use of the security deposit or part thereof.
Delay in replenishing the security deposit to the full amount for more than 7 days shall be considered a gross breach of obligations which entitles the lessor to terminate the lease agreement pursuant to Section 2288 of the Civil Code.
3. In the event that the tenant fails to return the apartment and equipment to the landlord at the end of the lease term in the condition in which he/she took it over, taking into account normal wear and tear, the security deposit shall be used to compensate the landlord for unjust enrichment and damages incurred by the landlord, in particular to restore the apartment to its original condition.
The landlord shall be entitled to claim from the tenant compensation for the costs of restoring the apartment and furnishings to their original condition if the security deposit was insufficient to cover them.
The tenant is obliged to pay these additional costs within 5 days from the date of the invoice.
4. In the event of termination of the lease, the landlord shall be obliged to account for the deposit to the tenant within 30 days of the termination of the lease and to return to the tenant the amount corresponding to the difference between the deposit and any debt of the tenant registered on the date of termination of the lease.
If the tenant has not incurred any debt to the landlord, the landlord is obliged to return the security deposit to the tenant in full.
V. Rights and Obligations of the Parties
1:
a. the right to payment of the agreed rent and service charges at the agreed time in due and timely manner, in accordance with this Agreement.
b. the right to enter the Apartment in order to check whether the Apartment is being used properly and to check whether there is any damage to the Apartment.
However, he shall be obliged to agree on the date of entry to the Apartment in advance.
c. the obligation to hand over the Apartment in a condition suitable for its use and to ensure the Tenant's undisturbed exercise of the rights associated with the use of the Apartment for the duration of the lease.
d. the obligation to remedy without undue delay any defects reported to it by the Tenant which prevent the proper use of the Apartment.
This provision shall not apply in the case of routine maintenance, minor defects or defects caused by the Tenant or persons occupying the Apartment.
2. In particular:
a. shall be entitled to use the Apartment only in accordance with its purpose, i.e. for living purposes, to maintain the Apartment in a proper manner and to carry out its routine maintenance and minor repairs at its own expense, to pay the agreed rent and payment for services properly and on time in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement,
b. not to carry out structural alterations, change the construction or character of the Apartment, i.e. not to make any substantial changes, even at his/her own expense, without the prior written consent of the Landlord,
c. shall notify the Landlord without undue delay of the need for such repairs to the Apartment as are to be borne by the Landlord and shall allow such repairs to be carried out.
In the event that the Landlord fails to remedy the defects or damages notified by the Tenant in a timely manner without undue delay and in a proper manner, the Tenant shall be entitled to remedy the same himself and to claim from the Landlord compensation for all costs reasonably incurred by the Tenant in remedying the same.
Should the defects or damage be of a substantial nature and affect the tenant's ability to properly use the apartment, the tenant shall also have the right to claim a reasonable reduction in the rent from the landlord for the period during which the defects or damage to the rental object lasted.
d. is obliged to hand over the Apartment to the Lessor on the date of termination of the lease, cleaned and tidy and in the condition in which he/she took over the Apartment, taking into account normal wear and tear with proper use and maintenance.
Any damage caused by the Tenant or those living in the Apartment with the Tenant shall be paid or repaired by the Landlord at the expense of the Tenant.
e. upon termination of the tenancy, neither the Tenant nor those sharing a household with the Tenant shall be entitled to a replacement Apartment, accommodation or shelter,
f. shall allow the Landlord to inspect the Apartment upon prior notice to the Tenant in order to verify that the Apartment is being used in a proper manner and to check for damage to the Apartment.
g. shall take special care to protect the furnishings and equipment of the Apartment
VI. Termination of the lease
1. the lease shall terminate in particular on expiry of the period for which it was agreed, by written agreement of the parties, or by the death of the tenant in accordance with the provisions of section 2279 an.
Civil Code.
2. The lease shall also end by written notice for the reasons and under the conditions set out in the Civil Code.
The notice period shall be 3 months and shall commence on the first day of the month following the month in which it is served.
3. The Tenant is obliged to vacate the Apartment at the end of the lease and to hand it over to the Landlord in a tidy condition, together with the accessories and equipment that he/she has taken over from the Landlord.
4. The Tenant is obliged to check out his/her possible residence from the Apartment until the end of the lease.
VII. Final arrangements
1. This Agreement shall come into force and effect on the date of its signing by both parties.
2. This Agreement is drawn up in 2 copies, each party receiving one copy.
