Strawberry, plum and invisible. Choose the right shade of lipstick: There's more than one red
When choosing a red lipstick, you should first determine whether you are a warm or cool type. Try a simple test - examine the veins on your wrist. If they are blue, you are a cold type, if they are green, you are a warm type. When choosing a new red lipstick, the first thing to do is to sort based on undertone. Only next consider the texture.
If you are a woman with a cool undertone, then purple, plum, cherry or mauve lipsticks are suitable for you.
If you fall into the category of warm skin undertones, choose lipsticks that are like that too. You can tell by the fact that they gravitate towards orange, coral, gold or brown shades.
You may find that some veins look green and others look blue. If that's the case, congratulate yourself - you don't have to look at the undertone and can just focus on your colour preferences.
